cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with network coding schemes and their performance in terms of throughput and decoding delay, which are key topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on network coding schemes and their implementation in network communication, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper discusses the performance of network coding schemes in terms of throughput and decoding delay, which are important metrics in social and information networks. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper proposes implementations of the coding framework to manage feedback frequency and coding complexity, which are related to computational complexity. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper provides simulations to verify the performance of the proposed coding schemes, which can be applied to multimedia communication.
